Former Manchester United defender Paul Parker has urged his former club not to sign Richarlison, insisting the Everton forward ‘lacks discipline’ and is ‘not trustworthy’. United are currently in the process of interviewing potential new managers with a new forward likely to be on the agenda this summer. Cristiano Ronaldo’s future at Old Trafford remains uncertain if the club fail to secure Champions League football next season with Edinson Cavani also likely to leave. Marcus Rashford meanwhile is considering his future with Anthony Martial deemed surplus to requirements in January, leaving to join Sevilla on loan. Mason Greenwood remains suspended by the club. Goal report United are now weighing up a move for Brazil international Richarlison with Everton currently scrapping for Premier League survival. Parker however insists the 27-year-old is not a good fit for United. ‘I don’t know who United will get as a manager, but Richarlison for me doesn’t really fit,’ Parker . ‘If you have a manager who can discipline him, because I think he lacks discipline. He’s not trustworthy. POLL ‘Wants to fall down all the time. Gets too emotional and gets involved in personal battles against people on the pitch. I would say no. I can’t really think of something positive.